 NIVA 声称 Live Nation 的“On The Road Again”活动损害了美国独立场馆https://www.nme.com/news/music/live-nations-on-the-road-again-campaign-harms-us-independent-venues-niva-claims-3515106?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=live-国家再次上路运动伤害美国独立场所尼瓦索赔Alex RigottiSun, 15 Oct 2023 11:32:04 +0000 Music NewsNewsLive Music News https://www.nme.com/?p=3515106 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/live-nation-ticketmaster-sued-class-action-lawsuit-2022@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Live Nation Ticketmaster 面临集体诉讼，被指控掠夺性行为" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/live-nation-ticketmaster-sued-class-action-lawsuit-2022@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/live-nation-ticketmaster-sued-class-action-lawsuit-2022@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/live-nation-ticketmaster-sued-class-action-lawsuit-2022@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/live-nation-ticketmaster-sued-class-action-lawsuit-2022@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/live-nation-ticketmaster-sued-class-action-lawsuit-2022@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/live-nation-ticketmaster-sued-class-action-lawsuit-2022@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> NIVA 表示，该活动将“将艺术家从独立场馆转移”，转而支持 Live Nation 运营的场馆</p><p><a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/live-nations-on-the-road-again-campaign-harms-us-independent-venues-niva-claims-3515106">NIVA 声称，Live Nation 的“On The Road Again”活动损害了美国独立场馆的利益，该声明</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/live-nation-ticketmaster-sued-class-action-lawsuit-2022@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Live Nation Ticketmaster 面临集体诉讼，被指控掠夺性行为" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/live-nation-ticketmaster-sued-class-action-lawsuit-2022@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/live-nation-ticketmaster-sued-class-action-lawsuit-2022@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/live-nation-ticketmaster-sued-class-action-lawsuit-2022@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/live-nation-ticketmaster-sued-class-action-lawsuit-2022@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/live-nation-ticketmaster-sued-class-action-lawsuit-2022@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/live-nation-ticketmaster-sued-class-action-lawsuit-2022@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>国家独立场馆协会 (NIVA) 发表声明，批评 Live Nation 为巡回演出艺术家提供经济支持的新活动。</p><ul><li><strong>了解更多：<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/live-nation-drop-merch-cuts-at-us-club-venues-3504606">数百家场所签署协议，不从艺术家的商品销售中抽取分成——但活动人士希望获得更多</a></strong></li></ul><p>作为 Live Nation“再次上路”计划的一部分，该<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/live-nation-drop-merch-cuts-at-us-club-venues-3504606">娱乐公司宣布将取消其在美国运营的所有场馆的商品折扣</a>。该活动于上个月（9 月 26 日）开始，还透露巡回演出的艺术家将获得 1500 美元（1,233 英镑）的津贴，以帮助支付燃料和旅行费用。该网站没有说明该计划将运行多长时间，仅指定“接下来的几个月”。</p><p> NIVA 在一份<a href="https://consequence.net/2023/09/live-nation-merch-cuts-independent-venues-niva/">新声明</a>中批评了该活动，称其将“将艺术家从独立场馆转移”，转而支持 Live Nation 运营的场馆。 NME 已联系 Live Nation 征求意见。</p><p>声明开头写道：“临时措施可能在短期内看似对艺术家有帮助，但实际上可能会挤出独立场地，而这些独立场地为许多利润微薄的艺术家提供了命脉。” “独立场馆和发起人每天都在投资和提升崭露头角的艺术家，NIVA 在全国范围内支持这些努力。昨天宣布的这一举措似乎是效仿一些独立场所的举措。事实并非如此。 </p><figure id="attachment_3131317" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3131317" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3131317" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/live-nation-ticketmaster-sued-class-action-lawsuit-2022@2000x1270.jpg" alt="Live Nation Ticketmaster 面临集体诉讼，被指控掠夺性行为" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/live-nation-ticketmaster-sued-class-action-lawsuit-2022@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/live-nation-ticketmaster-sued-class-action-lawsuit-2022@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/live-nation-ticketmaster-sued-class-action-lawsuit-2022@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/live-nation-ticketmaster-sued-class-action-lawsuit-2022@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/live-nation-ticketmaster-sued-class-action-lawsuit-2022@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/live-nation-ticketmaster-sued-class-action-lawsuit-2022@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3131317" class="wp-caption-text">洛杉矶的 Live Nation 设施于 2018 年拍摄。图片来源：Kristoffer Tripplaar / Alamy Stock Photo</figcaption></figure><p> NIVA 还指出，Live Nation 是一家“公开交易的企业集团”，拥有“不可估量的资源”，使其能够“将艺术家从独立场地转移出去，并进一步巩固对现场娱乐行业的控制”。他们表示，这威胁到“容量不足 3000 人的中小型场馆的活力，其中许多场馆仍在努力保持开放。</p><p>声明继续说道：“大多数艺术家、音乐家和喜剧演员开始职业生涯的独立舞台都是小型企业和非营利组织。他们不断面临成本上升、转售市场欺骗性票务行为增加以及全球大流行后持续存在的挑战。我们的舞台对于现场娱乐生态系统和当地经济至关重要，它们必须生存。</p><p> “对于艺术家和独立场馆来说，巡演的经济效益必须大幅提高。一定有更好的方法。 NIVA 将继续支持艺术家并为我们共同寻找的独立场馆提供支持。” </p><figure id="attachment_3399214" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3399214" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3399214" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/live-nation-logo.jpg" alt="现场国家" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/live-nation-logo.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/live-nation-logo-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/live-nation-logo-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/live-nation-logo-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/live-nation-logo-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/live-nation-logo-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3399214" class="wp-caption-text"> Live Nation 广告来源：Mario Tama/Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p>在英国，阻止场馆商品削减的斗争仍在继续。去年，特色艺术家联盟发起运动，允许艺术家从商品销售中获得 100% 的利润，这一活动得到了<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-charlatans">江湖骗子乐队的蒂姆·伯吉斯</a>( <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/tim-burgess">Tim Burgess)</a>的大力支持。</p><p> FAC 还管理着一个<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/fac-launches-database-of-venues-charging-zero-commission-on-merch-3141212">不从艺术家的商品利润中提成的场所名录</a>，场所可以通过填写表格进行注册。</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/live-nations-on-the-road-again-campaign-harms-us-independent-venues-niva-claims-3515106">NIVA 声称，Live Nation 的“On The Road Again”活动损害了美国独立场馆的利益，该声明</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
